5:
Sorry for calling you here so
suddenly. There's actually
something I need your help with.
8: I'd like you to have this.
12:
A concert ticket? You'd like for us to
help you out with the event?
15:
No, no. I want you to come watch
the concert! As audience members!
17:
I've been doing a lot of thinking and
research and finally managed to
put together a set list for the
concert. I'd like to get your honest
opinion!
22:
Oh come on, there's no need to be
so precise and stuff about this. Just
go with whatever feels right!
24:
And why'd you go and get me
involved in this? Why do I gotta
waste my time, exactly?!
28:
Because you're the leader! I think it's
the very least you could do.
31:
Like I said, go with your gut. If you
like how the set looks, that's that!
Simple stuff, really.
36:
So, you just want us to give our
opinions, right? Just so you know, I'm
not really an expert when it comes
to idols...
39:
Even just your brief thoughts would
be appreciated. I know it's a bit
outside your realm of expertise, but
I'd be grateful if you would humor
me!
45:
So, has anyone here actually been
to a Franchouchou concert before?
52:
Oh wow, thank you so much! But to
be honest, this isn't that big a
turnout...
55:
We've gotta put our ALL into this next
concert! That way, we can get even
MORE fans to come out next time!
57:
Okay, here goes our first song! I
hope you like it, everyone!
61:
Amazing. All that... twirling and
moving around, and they still
haven't run out of breath! Truly
impressive.
65:
Wow, it looks like they're even
syncing up their eye movements!
70:
Hmm... So, what'd you all think of the
performance?
74:
There's no doubt about it, you guys
are pros!
77:
You think so? Thank you! I'm so
happy to hear that.
84:
How was the concert? Tell me
exactly what you thought—no filter!
87:
It was quite the incredible
performance!
93:
Agreed! The rest of the audience
seemed to think so too! They were
pretty hyped during the whole thing.
97:
Right... I suppose that's what it
looked like to you guys.
101:
Huh? They're complimenting you,
dummy! That's supposed to make
you happy!
105:
I feel like ever since we came to this
Saga, our performances have been
lacking in some way.
107:
It's like we're not on the same
wavelength. It's been on my mind
for a while now...
110:
I mean, sometimes performances
don't go well. Everyone has off days,
right?
112:
It happens every once in a while.
This time's no different. Nothin' to
worry yourself about.
116:
I'm afraid it's not possible for me to
be so optimistic and carefree.
117:
I take my job as an idol very, very
seriously.
121: Yeah, yeah... I can see that.
125:
Tell me... What do you think was the
reason the crowd didn't get more
into the concert?
129:
Do you think it comes down to a
cultural difference? I feel like that's
just an excuse, though...
133:
Wow, you're really dedicated to your
craft, huh? I mean, I certainly
thought the performance was
awesome!
140:
I'm not at all knowledgeable about
the world of entertainment, but it
might be worth testing out this
hypothesis.
145:
This device lets you navigate
between different worlds, right?
What does it have to do with our
concerts?
150:
For me, having the opportunity to
travel to new worlds was an
immensely valuable experience.
152:
I felt that might be the case for you
too. At the very least, it should
provide you with some inspiration.
157:
Okay. It's certainly better than sitting
around and doing nothing!
158:
I'm off tomorrow, so I'll take the day
to travel with you guys!
164:
Ooh, now that's what I'm talking
about! All right, are we okay to meet
up here?
168:
Wait a minute. Saki, do you actually
want to come with us?
171:
Uh, yeah? What happened to that
whole "you're the leader" crap? Here
I am, acting as a leader! Unless
someone has a problem with me
comin' along.
175:
I see no problems with it. The more
the merrier.
179:
Awesome. I'm actually kinda
psyched to see how this turns out!
187:
Don't forget we're doing this for the
sake of the group!
